
Overview of verb need

The verb need has 3 senses (first 3 from tagged texts)
                                           
1. (110) necessitate, ask, postulate, need, require, take, involve, call for, demand -- (require as useful, just, or proper; "It takes nerve to do what she did"; "success usually requires hard work"; "This job asks a lot of patience and skill"; "This position demands a lot of personal sacrifice"; "This dinner calls for a spectacular dessert"; "This intervention does not postulate a patient's consent")
2. (98) want, need, require -- (have need of; "This piano wants the attention of a competent tuner")
3. (1) need -- (have or feel a need for; "always needing friends and money")
